working/validation/validation.go`):\n- `validateHTTPIngressPath()`: **Requires pathType field** with validation at line 428-429: `if path.PathType == nil { return append(allErrs, field.Required(...))}`\n- `IngressValidationOptions`: Struct handling beta-to-GA transitions including `AllowInvalidSecretName` and `AllowInvalidWildcardHostRule` flags\n- `ValidateIngressCreate()`: Sets strict validation options\n- `ValidateIngressUpdate()`: Allows backwards compatibility by checking old Ingress object to permit previously invalid data\n\n### 4. Default Values\n\n**v1 Defaults** (`pkg/apis/networking/v1/defaults.go`):\n- No SetDefaults_HTTPIngressPath function\n- pathType is **required, not optional**\n- No default value provided\n\n**v1beta1 Defaults** (`pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/defaults.go`):\n- `SetDefaults_HTTPIngressPath()`: Sets default pathType to PathTypeImplementationSpecific when nil\n- Enables smooth migration from v1beta1 to v1\n\n### 5. Storage and Registry\n\n**Storage Version** (`pkg/registry/networking/rest/storage_settings.go`):\n- v1 is the storage version (RESTStorage maps to v1)\n- v1beta1 continues to be served via API but converts to/from v1 for storage\n- SetVersionPriority in install.go: v1 has highest priority, then v1beta1, then v1alpha1\n\n**Ingress Strategy** (`pkg/registry/networking/ingress/strategy.go`):\n- Validates both v1 and v1beta1 versions\n- `Validate()` method calls `validation.ValidateIngressCreate()`\n- `ValidateUpdate()` handles backwards compatibility\n- API versions tracked: \"extensions/v1beta1\", \"networking.k8s.io/v1beta1\", \"networking.k8s.io/v1\"\n\n**Ingress REST Storage** (`pkg/registry/networking/ingress/storage/storage.go`):\n- Uses internal networking.Ingress type for storage\n- Conversion happens transparently at API boundaries\n\n### 6. API Installation\n\n**Installation** (`pkg/apis/networking/install/install.go`):\n- `Install()` registers: v1 (highest priority), v1beta1, v1alpha1\n- Version priority ensures v1 is preferred for storage and response\n\n### 7. Tests\n\n**Conversion Tests** (`pkg/apis/networking/v1beta1/conversion_test.go`):\n- Tests backend conversion (ServiceName/ServicePort ↔ Service)\n- Validates round-trip conversions between v1beta1 and internal types\n\n**Validation Tests** (`pkg/apis/networking/validation/validation_test.go`):\n- Tests pathType validation and support for all PathType values\n- Tests invalid pathType handling\n\n## Migration Summary\n\nThe migration from v1beta1 to v1 involves:\n1. **pathType becomes required**: v1 has no omitempty, v1beta1 defaults to ImplementationSpecific\n2. **Backend field deprecated**: v1beta1's Backend (with ServiceName/ServicePort) converts to v1's Service field\n3. **Validation enforcement**: v1 requires pathType; v1beta1 allows omitting it with default\n4. **Storage unification**: v1 is the storage version; v1beta1 requests convert to v1 for persistence\n5. **Backwards compatibility**: ValidateUpdate allows previously invalid data in existing Ingress objects\n"
